@*
 * ============================================================================
 * DotNet Bookstore — In-Class ASP.NET Core MVC Project
 * Course: COMP2084 | Georgian College | Summer 2026
 * Instructor: Dario Hesami
 * ============================================================================
 *
 * FILE:    Views/Shared/_ValidationScriptsPartial.cshtml
 * PURPOSE: A reusable partial view that loads the two JavaScript libraries
 *          needed for client-side (browser) form validation. It is included
 *          inside the @section Scripts { } block of any form view.
 *
 * KEY CONCEPTS FOR STUDENTS:
 *  1. Client-side validation    — runs in the browser BEFORE the form is
 *                                 submitted, giving users instant feedback
 *                                 without a round-trip to the server.
 *                                 Example: required fields highlighted red
 *                                 immediately when the user tabs out.
 *  2. Server-side validation    — also ALWAYS runs in the controller
 *                                 (ModelState.IsValid check). Client-side
 *                                 validation is a convenience, not a security
 *                                 guarantee — a user can disable JavaScript.
 *  3. jquery.validate           — a jQuery plug-in that reads HTML5 validation
 *                                 attributes (required, minlength, maxlength,
 *                                 pattern, etc.) and validates on the fly.
 *  4. jquery.validate.unobtrusive — Microsoft's adapter that bridges
 *                                 ASP.NET Core's data-val-* HTML attributes
 *                                 (generated by Tag Helpers like asp-validation-for)
 *                                 with the jQuery Validation plug-in.
 *                                 "Unobtrusive" means validation rules are
 *                                 embedded in HTML attributes rather than
 *                                 inline JavaScript, keeping HTML and JS separate.
 *
 * HOW IT IS USED:
 *   In any form view (e.g., Books/Create.cshtml) you will see:
 *     @section Scripts {
 *         @{ await Html.RenderPartialAsync("_ValidationScriptsPartial"); }
 *     }
 *   This injects these two script tags into the "Scripts" section of _Layout.cshtml,
 *   which is rendered after jQuery (a required dependency) is already loaded.
 * ============================================================================
 *@

@* jquery.validate: core validation engine *@
<script src="~/lib/jquery-validation/dist/jquery.validate.min.js"></script>

@* jquery.validate.unobtrusive: bridges ASP.NET Core's data-val-* HTML attributes
   (produced by Tag Helpers) to jquery.validate, enabling automatic validation
   without any custom JavaScript in the view *@
<script src="~/lib/jquery-validation-unobtrusive/dist/jquery.validate.unobtrusive.min.js"></script>
